<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>

<worksheet >
    <title>GR-5 Modeling Systems</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete all four problems to get M. Complete any three problems to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
      <p>A carpentry shop produces two types of wooden furniture: Chairs and Tables. Manufacturing 
        requires two primary resources: labor hours and wood supply. Each Chair requires 2 hours 
        of labor and 4 board-feet of wood. Each Table requires 3 hours of labor and 9 board-feet 
        of wood. The shop has a maximum of 60 hours of labor and 144 board-feet of wood available 
        each week. The shop wants to maximize the total number of furniture pieces produced.</p>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in"><statement><p>Set up a system of linear inequalities whose graph 
        would represent all possible combinations of Chairs and Tables that satisfy the 
        constraints.</p></statement></exercise>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in"><statement><p>Find the solution region. Be sure to give a complete graph.</p></statement></exercise>
  </page>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1in"><statement><p>Setup the objective function.</p></statement></exercise>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in"><statement><p>Find the maximum number of Chairs and Tables that 
      the shop can produce based on the constraints.</p></statement></exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>